'''''Star Wars Insider'' 64''' is the sixty-fourth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[December 3]], [[2002]]. Issue 64 marked the return of ''[[Bantha Tracks (department)|Bantha Tracks]]'', the official [[Hyperspace: The Official Star Wars Fan Club|''Star Wars'' Fan Club]] newsletter, which was published quarterly on the back side of subscriber-exclusive editions of ''Star Wars Insider'' through [[Star Wars Insider 75|issue 75]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*From the Editor's Desk {{C|by [[Dave Gross]]}}
*[[Rebel Rumblings]]
*[[Star News]]: From the World of Lucasfilm {{C|by [[Benjamin Harper]]}}
*[[The Jawa Trader|Jawa Trader]]
*[[Comics Link]] &mdash; [[Star Wars: Jedi (one-shots)|''Star Wars'': Jedi]] {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*[[Bookshelf]] &mdash; Boba Fett's Greatest Hits {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*[[Gamescape]]
**''Star Wars'' Galaxies Update {{C|by [[W. Haden Blackman|Haden Blackman]]}}
**''[[Coruscant and the Core Worlds]]'' {{C|by Daniel Wallace}}
*[[Set Piece]]: Ewok Village {{C|by [[Chris Reiff]] and [[Chris Trevas|Christopher Trevas]]}}
*[[Scouting the Galaxy]] &mdash; Strange Tales From the ''Star Wars'' Fashion Frontier {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*[[Crossword (department)|Crossword]] &mdash; Satire Wars {{C|by [[Michael Selinker|Mike Selinker]]}}
*[[Star Wars Q&A|''Star Wars'' Q&A]] {{C|by Pablo Hidalgo}}
*[[The Last Page]]

===Features===
*"[[Prequel Update]]" {{C|by [[Dave Gross]]}}
*:<small>[[Rick McCallum]] talks building sets and designing costumes.</small>
*"[[Clones to the IMAX: Star Wars Hits the Bigger Screen|''Clones'' to the IMAX: ''Star Wars'' Hits the Bigger Screen]]" {{C|by [[David C. Fein]]}}
*:<small>Peek behind the eight-story curtain and see how this fall's limited release of {{Film|II}}&mdash;''The IMAX Experience'' came about.</small>
*"[[Inside Attack of the Clones|Inside ''Attack of the Clones'']]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>Obi-Wan's Geonosian prison cell is the battlefield for a contest of wills between two masters of the Force.</small>
*"[[Dream Weavers: The People of Industrial Light & Magic]]" {{C|by Dave Gross with [[Pablo Hidalgo]]}}
*:<small>Meet [[John Knoll]], [[Paul Huston]], and [[Ben Snow]], three key members of the Industrial Light & Magic team responsible for the eye-popping visual effects of Episode II.</small>
*"[[Feedback Loop: Ben Burtt in 30 Years of Star Wars Sounds]]" {{C|by [[Francis K. Lalumière]]}}
*:<small>Ben Burtt discuses the family of sounds that make up the ''Star Wars'' audio experience.</small>
*"[[The Vehicles of Episode II]]" {{C|by [[Daniel Wallace]]}}
*:<small>This latest installment in ''Insider''{{'s}} ongoing series zooms in on the speeders, walker and sundry other modes of transport from ''Attack of the Clones''.</small>
*"[[Emissary of the Void]]": Episode VI {{C|by [[Greg Keyes]]}}
*:<small>Can Uldir Lochet stop the Yuuzhan Vong plan to cripple the New Republic, or will he unwittingly help them? The exciting conclusion to The New Jedi Order serial adventure.</small>
*"[[Insider's Holiday Gift Guide|''Insider''{{'s}} Holiday Gift Guide]]" {{C|by [[Michael Mikaelian]]}}
*:<small>The ''Star Wars Insider'' staff picks our favorite holiday gifts for ''Star Wars'' fans everywhere.</small>

